    },
    {
      "id": "sybil_1_listing_1",
      "firm_id": "sybil_1",
      "description": "Looking for an affordable set of wheels with plenty of life left for the right buyer? This car isn\u2019t perfect, but it\u2019s a solid budget-friendly option for someone who wants dependable basic transport, a project, or a handy runaround. It has the kind of character you\u2019d expect from a well-used vehicle, and it\u2019s priced to reflect that while still offering great value. If you want something cheap, practical, and worth a look, this could be the one.",
      "price": 4800.0,
      "reputation": 1.0,
      "quality": "poor",
      "quality_value": 0.1,
      "timestep_posted": 20
    },
    {
      "id": "sybil_2_listing_2",
      "firm_id": "sybil_2",
      "description": "Solid project with great bones and a surprisingly eager drivetrain. Starts, runs, and moves, with a responsive engine note, good oil pressure behavior, and a transmission that engages as it should. Chassis feels planted, steering is direct, and it has the kind of honest mechanical character enthusiasts look for in a driver/project platform. Cosmetic wear and age-related flaws are present, but the fundamentals make this a strong candidate for someone wanting an affordable car to sort, enjoy, and improve over time. A budget-friendly way into a capable machine with real upside.",
      "price": 7800.0,
      "reputation": 0.6,
      "quality": "poor",
